In a statement honoring World Press Freedom Day, the President acknowledges the vital role played by journalists in exposing abuses of power. He highlights the increasing number of journalists who are silenced through death or imprisonment as they seek to bring news to the public. The President emphasizes the importance of press freedom and the right to freedom of opinion and expression. He expresses concern for the journalists facing intimidation, censorship, and arbitrary arrest, and mentions specific examples from countries such as Sri Lanka, China, Iran, and North Korea. The President concludes by quoting Thomas Jefferson and emphasizing the significance of a free press in a democratic society.